Hello all!

Our team is working on refining our autons ready for our next competition.

Right now we have a reliable four note auton and we’d like to make it a little more reliable using neural net detection on a Coral and Limelight. We are java command based swerve robot using Path Planner.

Last year in Charged Up, when we tried to do some auto alignment in auton and Path Planner didn’t seem to want to give up control of the drivetrain.

Has anyone had any luck doing this and could point us in the right direction?

Thanks!

Our team created a vision targeting command solely for autonomous that controlled speed and direction, then created a path in PathPlanner that was a little shorter than the target goal. After that we just put them in a sequential group (path first, then note targeting). However we are using Photonvision running on OrangePi instead of a Coral so I don’t know if that would change anything
